#
# usage of doctest in python
#
1) doctest can do unit test in python too, similar to unittest.

2) a basic example
    def show_me_the_money():
        """
        >>> print show_me_the_money()
        $
        """
        return '$'

    if __name__ == '__main__':
        import doctest
        doctest.testmod()

3) can seperate test cases and source code by put the docstring into a .py file,
        and test cases into another .py file.

# ref:  Python中的单元测试  http://pm.readthedocs.io/unittest/python.html#doctest
